id><gtr:firstName>Andrew</gtr:firstName><gtr:surname>Kerr</gtr:surname><gtr:roles><gtr:role><gtr:name>PRINCIPAL_INVESTIGATOR</gtr:name></gtr:role></gtr:roles></gtr:personRole></gtr:personRoles><gtr:project url="http://gtr.ukri.org:80/projects?ref=RES-173-27-0055"><gtr:id>48D0E04B-63C4-40F4-A7A7-C5B5330DF0E8</gtr:id><gtr:title>Climate Change Adaption Placement Fellowship</gtr:title><gtr:status>Closed</gtr:status><gtr:grantCategory>Fellowship</gtr:grantCategory><gtr:grantReference>RES-173-27-0055</gtr:grantReference><gtr:abstractText>The project aims to analyse and characterise current &amp;quot;climate adaptation&amp;quot; activity in Scotland (including public sector, private sector and non-governmental organisations).&amp;nbsp; The outputs will feed in to the forthcoming Scottish Climate Adaptation Strategy.&amp;nbsp; The project encompasses:
&lt;br />
&lt;br />
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>what activities are enhancing resilience to the changing weather patterns?&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>who is and who isn't enhancing their resilience to climate change?&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>why are some sectors more successful at developing resilience strategies than others?&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>what gaps and barriers exist that affect the development of resilience strategies?&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;br />Key elements of the project include:
&lt;br />
&lt;br />
&lt;ul>
 &lt;li>defining what constitutes climate adaptation for different organisations&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>characterising different risk management strategies by organisations&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>investigating the existing adaptive capacity of different organisations&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>exploring social and technical barriers to uptake of adaptive activities&lt;/li>
 &lt;li>understanding the role of the current policy landscape in enhancing or restricting the development of resilience strategies for a changing climate&lt;/li>
